originalText.text: Rarely feel compelled to write a review, but I enjoyed my experience with Honeybreak Officiants so thoroughly that it would be wrong not to share with other couples. Throwing a wedding together in a week is obviously stressful, but Celine took a lot of the burden off my shoulders by being so considerate and knowledgeable. She answered all of my questions and made me feel at ease during the planning process - even providing an extensive list of sample vows! She came to our home to perform the ceremony and her words made me so emotional. Just so lovely! She also took some of the best photos of the night if you don't hire a photographer. Big fans!!! Highly recommend.

originalText.text: We came across Honeybreak on The Knot while searching for an officiant for our small wedding. Celine was already highly commended by previous reviews so we mentioned her name when submitting our quote request. After our introductory Zoom meeting, we were confident that we made the right choice. We had only a general idea of the kind of ceremony we wanted at first, but Celine helped guide us through the customization process in a fun and stress-free way. Once we provided her with some details about ourselves and our story, she put together a wonderful ceremony that was so well written and felt so natural, some of our guests assumed that she'd known us for years. Celine is kind, poised, and has great presence -- our wedding day was perfect and we could not be happier that she was a part of it. Cheers!

originalText.text:
We originally saw honeybreak officiants on wedding wire, when looking we really wanted an officiant that was comfortable marrying anyone regardless of race, gender or nationality. Celine went above and beyond for us before, during and even after the ceremony. She made sure we knew exactly what to expect at every step and helped us carry out the elopement of our dreams. She customized the ceremony by having a zoom call with us and getting us to fill out an incredibly beautiful survey and surprised us with the most beautiful words and life promises to each other. She also gave us many tips and links for places to get married in the location we wanted in NYC, vow tips as well as the steps we would need to take afterwards.
Thank you Celine for everything you truly made getting married internationally a breeze!

originalText.text:
Celine was the perfect officiant for our beautiful NYC wedding. She wrote and helped provide us with a personalised ceremony that was very special and matched the tone we wanted for our wedding completely.

She was also very helpful providing us extra marriage information as we are not US citizens.

originalText.text: My wife and I thought finding an officiant would be one of the simpler aspects of planning our wedding, but when we sat down and started looking for one, we quickly realized just how much more there was to consider than we realized. From the order of events, to the rituals and ceremonies, to the degree of religiosity, there were so many angles to consider and, more than that, questions we didn’t even know that we should be asking. Enter Honeybreak officiants, and specifically Celine, who was our patient, kind, knowledgable, flexible guide through all of these points and so much more. Celine truly gave us the ceremony we had been dreaming of, and we knew within moments of sitting down to speak with her for the first time that she was the officiant for us. One thing we learned while searching for our officiant was that they oftentimes come prepared with a vision of how the ceremony will go. When we listened to them describe their services, we could feel almost immediately that it was not the right fit for us— either too starched, too religious, or conversely lacking in any traditional elements. Not so with Celine. We gave her a few scant ideas and images of what we wanted for our ceremony, more a vibe than anything else, and she gave us back a fully formatted and beautifully moving ceremony, featuring all of the events and moments we asked for and none that we didn’t. In short, she got us. She knew exactly what we were looking for after talking to us for maybe half an hour. More than that, she continued to work with us to refine our plan, being flexible with wording and offering advice whenever needed, but always making sure our special day was just that: special and uniquely ours. I really can’t say enough about the great work Celine did, but if our testimony is not enough, we had friends and family members coming up to us all throughout the reception telling us how wonderful and moving they found the ceremony to be. We could not be more pleased to have entrusted such a delicate thing as the moment of our marriage to Celine!
